<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-47-0862 </DOCNO><TEXT>Cited are the results of an investigation carried out by ENEA to determinethe social-economic impact of a nuclear power station located in an agriculturalarea in northern Italy. Statistical data were collected to trace theevolution of local agriculture from 1961 to 1985, the third year afterreactor start-up. The data and analysis showed that the growth behaviourreflected national and international trends without any evidence of localinfluence. The study also showed that the impact of increased local populationduring the construction phase of the nuclear station was moderate.</TEXT></DOC>